event.content:
Donuts And Dipsticks in Placentia are cars and coffee events.  They’re intimate and open to everyone and every type of vehicle.

When I attended someone even had a 1970’s Honda Trail 70.  And it was in like-new condition.  All C&C events are family-friendly and this one is for sure too.

In fact, I think most of the guys there knew each other’s names.  But that didn’t stop them from welcoming me.  As I jumped right into a couple of different conversations and enjoyed some laughs.

It’s held every Saturday morning in the parking lot of Kenny’s Donuts.  But be careful.  Because it’s a Kenny’s Donuts in Placentia.

Naturally, Kenny’s Donuts is open and serving fresh java, donuts, and more.  And even feel comfortable bringing our family’s four-legged friend to the show.

Our dog, Mr. Jake, can be quite sensitive to rumbling motors.  But this is pretty laid back.  It’s just off of Orangethorpe Avenue.  And maybe a mile-ish from the 90/91 intersection.

 

Everyone and every-vehicle welcomed!

Donuts And Dipsticks Cars And Coffee Events

Dates: Every Saturday Morning
Location: Kenny’s Donuts Placentia – 2001 E. Orangethorpe Ave. Placentia, CA
Starts: 7 AM
Ends: 9 AM
Admission: Free
Vehicle Registration: Free

*Please note: iDriveSoCal does not host this event.  So if you’d like to learn more about the event please contact event organizers HERE.  And that includes more specific details about attending, displaying your vehicle, and becoming a vendor or sponsor.
